result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Derick Thomas Huebner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Fox, ADA:  Alexis S Mckinley, DF ATTY:  John A Kucinski, DF:  Derick Thomas Huebner appeared. Defendant's mother also appears. There is not an agreement and a trial date is requested. Defendant's mother makes statements to the Court. Recess. Case recalled at 4:30 p.m. There is an agreement. ADA Nieskes recites agreement. Court reviews constitutional rights with def. Court finds def freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights. Court reads charge and possible penalties for counts 1, 2 & 3. Def pleads no contest to counts 1, 2 & 3. Court uses complaints/reports as factual basis, accepts plea and adjudicates def guilty of counts 2 & 3. Court STAYS the adjudication in count 1 pending full performance of the DJOC. 
Court orders in counts 2 & 3, concurrent: S/W 2 years probation with conditions: 
- 10 days in St. Croix County Jail; IMPOSED & STAYED. To be used at the discretion of the probation agent
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- Pay restitution of $800.00; joint and several with co-defendant's.
- Defendant is approved to go to school in Arizona 
- Defendant is approved to travel to Mexico for a family vacation (upon agreement of probation agent)
- Write a valid and meaningful apology letter within 30 days.
- Court costs for each count for $243.00 ($486.00 total) Payable through probation.
Probation may be transferred to Arizona. 
Defendant to sign up for probation and the DA's office (re: agreement) on 6/27/2014. Defendant is advised of right to appeal. 
Court reviews DJOC for count one. Bond continues during the 2 year agreement. Court approves and signs agreement.

-Bond is to be Co-Signed by Robin Huebner     

-Defendant to reside with his parents 160 3rd Street Glenwood City, WI under house arrest.

-Defendant to continue with school and Counselor visits (mother to drive him to and from school/appointments).

-It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, John M.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
